^Vince


I will make sure you get on this distribution list.


Credit is going to be a big issue for energy companies and banks.


We may need to form additional discussion groups.


Volatility in energy prices and a general economic slowdown may cause an

increase in defaults.


Banks are primarily interested in regulatory impact on loan portfolio and

credit derivatives as a an alternative to raising capital or selling assets.


Energy companies could use credit derivatives to hedge or price credit

exposure.


Don Mumma(ex CSFB, MD Axiom Software)is organizing a survey of energy credit

practices. You can reach Don at 212-248-4188 ext 22.


Regards,


Philip Merrill

